217
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:51,140
So typography is a very
sort of vast subject.

218
00:08:51,140 --> 00:08:52,670
It has a lot of details in it.

219
00:08:52,670 --> 00:08:54,080
And I can't cover
them all today.

220
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,790
But what I highly,
highly recommend

221
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:59,060
you do is go to
practicaltypography.com.

222
00:08:59,060 --> 00:09:02,223
This is a completely free,
open-source online book

223
00:09:02,223 --> 00:09:03,890
that will basically
teach you everything

224
00:09:03,890 --> 00:09:06,260
you could need to
know about typography

225
00:09:06,260 --> 00:09:07,520
in a very concise way.

226
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:09,920
It'll take about three hours
to read cover to cover.

227
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:12,590
And it will vastly improve
the design of everything

228
00:09:12,590 --> 00:09:14,840
that you write.

229
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:17,840
But I do want to touch a
little bit on fonts, hierarchy,

230
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:21,380
and a couple of dataviz
specific concerns.

231
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:24,560
So the font that you choose
really matters in a chart.

232
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:27,958
It especially affects the
tone of your graphic, right?

233
00:09:27,958 --> 00:09:29,750
You can send a completely
different message

234
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:32,150
based on the font you choose.

235
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:34,850
And it can also really affect
the legibility of your graphic,

236
00:09:34,850 --> 00:09:35,990
right?

237
00:09:35,990 --> 00:09:38,502
It's pretty easy to
have misunderstandings

238
00:09:38,502 --> 00:09:39,710
if you choose the wrong font.

239
00:09:42,850 --> 00:09:43,620
This is important.

240
00:09:46,140 --> 00:09:48,720
And the unfortunate thing is
that most people will just

241
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:51,790
go for the system
font-- the default font.

242
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:54,630
And that's sad because
most system fonts

243
00:09:54,630 --> 00:09:55,490
are pretty terrible.

244
00:09:55,490 --> 00:09:56,790
I'm sorry to tell you.

245
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:58,980
Most of them were
designed for the screens

246
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:00,990
that we had in the
1990s, which were

247
00:10:00,990 --> 00:10:02,430
all pixilated and terrible.

248
00:10:02,430 --> 00:10:05,312
And on modern screens,
they look pretty ugly.

249
00:10:05,312 --> 00:10:07,020
So if you're a
professional organization,

250
00:10:07,020 --> 00:10:08,515
you might buy a
professional font.

251
00:10:08,515 --> 00:10:10,140
But for most of you
in the room, you'll

