260
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:37,770
So next, I want to touch a
little bit upon hierarchy--

261
00:10:37,770 --> 00:10:40,450
a typographic hierarchy.

262
00:10:40,450 --> 00:10:42,330
So a typographic
hierarchy is just

263
00:10:42,330 --> 00:10:45,420
a way of encoding an
order of importance

264
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:47,310
in your type that
helps to navigate

265
00:10:47,310 --> 00:10:51,385
your readers through your
chart or through your document.

266
00:10:51,385 --> 00:10:53,260
And there's several ways
to create hierarchy.

267
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:55,410
So this is a case
where we have none.

268
00:10:55,410 --> 00:10:58,530
The easiest way to create
hierarchy is with size.

269
00:10:58,530 --> 00:11:00,780
But you can also do
it with font weight,

270
00:11:00,780 --> 00:11:04,080
with color, with spacing.

271
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:07,320
You can do it with a
contrasting typeface,

272
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:10,500
or, ideally, a combination
of all of these things.

273
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:12,810
And learning the rules of
how to create a hierarchy,

274
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:15,030
you know, what should
you make your title

275
00:11:15,030 --> 00:11:17,130
versus your subtitle
versus your body text

276
00:11:17,130 --> 00:11:19,830
is just a skill that takes
a little bit of practice.

277
00:11:19,830 --> 00:11:21,450
But there are some
more specific tips

278
00:11:21,450 --> 00:11:25,348
