314
00:12:49,630 --> 00:12:53,910
So the color wheel like we
all know from grade school--

315
00:12:53,910 --> 00:12:55,500
it looks like this.

316
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:57,703
And there's several
types of palettes

317
00:12:57,703 --> 00:13:00,120
you can choose from the color
wheel that will usually have

318
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:02,680
colors that go well together.

319
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:04,752
So if you want to choose
a high contrast palette,

320
00:13:04,752 --> 00:13:06,210
you can choose a
complementary one.

321
00:13:06,210 --> 00:13:09,207
That means opposite
sides of the color wheel.

322
00:13:09,207 --> 00:13:11,040
You can also choose
analogous color palettes

323
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:13,743
which all come from the same
side of the color wheel.

324
00:13:13,743 --> 00:13:15,660
And there's triadic which
are sort of laid out

325
00:13:15,660 --> 00:13:17,370
in a triangle like this.

326
00:13:17,370 --> 00:13:21,540
And there's several other
color palettes as well.

327
00:13:21,540 --> 00:13:25,070
There's split complementary,
quadratic, and lots of others.

328
00:13:25,070 --> 00:13:27,570
And you can read a little bit
more about sort of the feeling

329
00:13:27,570 --> 00:13:29,010
that all these color
palettes give you.

330
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:31,302
But this is a nice way to
sort of get started if you're

331
00:13:31,302 --> 00:13:34,152
looking to choose some hues.

332
00:13:34,152 --> 00:13:35,610
So once you choose
those, you might

333
00:13:35,610 --> 00:13:37,277
